The kitchen is the heart of the house. For families a clean, well working kitchen is important and to the young professional a stylish kitchen is vital not just to their aspiring lifestyle and image but could be considered a social point of the home. Remove that old clutter and clean till both hands are raw. Turn lights on and open curtains and blinds as fully as you possibly can, the mantra for a good kitchen is clean and bright. You may make relatively cheap and substantial improvements towards the look of your kitchen by changing cupboard doors. Painting or staining them to light colours could be a cheaper alternative. Handles and knobs could be replaced to enhance any kitchen; the possibilities are dependent on budget. If you have a kitchen-diner set a little, clean but sophisticated place setting.

Bright and clean also applies to bathrooms. Luxury bathrooms add value along with a focal point to a home but this may not be possible given budget considerations. However, there really is no excuse for a dingy bathroom. A lot of homes available on the market with horrible bathrooms might be replaced and sold for a higher price immediately, a lick of paint, a good clean or perhaps a second-hand bathroom set can vastly improve the bathroom. Fresh flower bouquets perform a lot for a bathroom, both in appearance and aroma.

Finally the bedrooms. Use soft, neutral colours, earth tones are always safe. Limit furniture, remove desks otherwise needed unless the bedrooms are large. Even removing clothing from wardrobes can be advisable just in case someone has a snoop. Cramped wardrobes suggest limited storage. Luxurious bedding and accent pillows can add a genuine sense of luxury to the home and give it that little bit extra appeal that could be needed. Again, de-clutter and remove personal photos, the buyer really wants to see themselves in the room, not you or your kids.

In conclusion, de-clutter, clean, neutralize and if you have the budget improve kitchens, bathrooms as well as rent furniture for living spaces. Do this and your house will sell faster and for a greater value.